To turn this mock-up into a colorful and interactive website, you can use HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Here's a basic outline of the steps you can take:

1. Create a new HTML file and add the following code to define the structure of the website:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<title>My Joke Website</title>
	<style>
		body {
			background-color: #f2f2f2;
			font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
			text-align: center;
			padding: 20px;
		}
		h1 {
			color: #333;
			font-size: 36px;
			margin-bottom: 20px;
		}
		p {
			color: #666;
			font-size: 18px;
			margin-bottom: 20px;
		}
		a {
			color: #333;
			text-decoration: none;
		}
		a:hover {
			color: #f00;
		}
	</style>
</head>
<body>
	<h1>My Joke Website</h1>
	<p>
		<a href="#">Push to reveal punchline?</a>
	</p>
</body>
</html>
```
1. Add a JavaScript file to the website, and use the following code to replace the joke with a real joke when the user clicks the "Push to reveal punchline?" link:
```javascript
document.getElementById("push-to-reveal-punchline").addEventListener("click", function() {
	var punchline = "Why was the math book sad? Because it had too many problems.";
	document.getElementById("punchline").innerHTML = punchline;
});
```
1. Finally, add a new image to the website, and use the following code to display the image when the user clicks the "Push to reveal punchline?" link:
```javascript
document.getElementById("push-to-reveal-punchline").addEventListener("click", function() {
	var image = new Image();
	image.src = "path/to/image.jpg";
	image.onload = function() {
		document.getElementById("punchline").innerHTML = "";
		document.getElementById("image").src = image.src;
	};
});
```
Replace "path/to/image.jpg" with the actual path to the image you want to display.

This is just a basic outline of how you can turn the mock-up into a colorful and interactive website. You can add more features and styles to the website as needed.
